# App chrome layout — protected (do not regress)

**User-confirmed good state (2026-06-18).** Read `memory-bank/app-chrome-layout-protected-state.md` before editing header, task progress, or side rail layout.

## Invariants

| Area | Rule |
|------|------|
| Task progress | In **document flow** after `.scene-controls-row`; never `position: fixed` over header |
| App content | No `.has-progress` margin hack — flex layout handles progress bar height |
| Right rail top | `.opennexus-sidebar` uses measured `--app-content-top` on `:root`, not chrome calc alone |
| CSS vars | Do **not** define `--app-content-top` on `.app` (shadows measured px value) |
| Collapsed rails | Mirror left/right via shared `--collapsed-rail-*` tokens and paired selectors |
| Z-index | Side panels ≤ 998; fix overlap by adjusting `top`, not raising panel z-index |

## Forbidden without explicit user request

- Fixed task bar with hardcoded `top` (e.g. `52px`) or z-index above header band.
- Right rail `top: var(--app-chrome-top-height)` without `--app-content-top`.
- Asymmetric collapsed-rail `padding-top` on one side only.
- Removing `TaskAdvancedOptions` import from `TaskManager.jsx`.

## Protected files

`App.jsx`, `App.css`, `TaskProgressBar.jsx`, `TaskProgressBar.css`, `TaskManager.jsx` (import)

## Before merging layout touches

Visual check: both rails collapsed — icon rows align; running task — bar below scene-controls, header clickable, rails still aligned.
